item.title: [HIVE-19806] Several tests do not properly sort their output
item.description: A number of the tests produce unsorted output that happens to come out the same on people's laptops and the ptest infrastructure.  But when run on a separate linux box the sort differences show up.
item.summary: Several tests do not properly sort their output

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

gates I have few questions:
1. Why did TestMetaStoreMetrics have to sleep?
2. Bunch of tests are removed from testconfiguration. Are these disabled tests?

Bunch of tests are removed from testconfiguration. Are these disabled tests?

They are qfiles that aren't there anymore.  People just forgot to remove them from testconfiguration.

Why did TestMetaStoreMetrics have to sleep?

Since it requires a call from the client to the metastore in a different thread the we have to make sure the current thread yields and the metastore thread gets a chance to process the close request.
